This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically on accelerating separable convolutions in efficient convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel decomposition approach based on SVD, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the proposed approach, which is related to artificial intelligence and decision making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions conducting experiments with the latest ShuffleNet V2 model, which is related to multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a method for accelerating convolutional neural networks, which is related to neural networks and deep learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
